title: Buxo da Rocha
body: The people of Madeira give this name to the Catha Dryandri, a shrub of the Celastraceae family, and to the Chamaemeles coriácea, a shrub of the Rosaceae family. The first of these shrubs can be found in S. Gonçalo, Seixal, etc.; the second near the Câmara Pestana Asylum, in Praia Formosa, etc.

S. Gonçalo: Location where the shrub Catha Dryandri can be found
Seixal: Location where the shrub Catha Dryandri can be found
Câmara Pestana Asylum: Location where the shrub Chamaemeles coriácea can be found
Praia Formosa: Location where the shrub Chamaemeles coriácea can be found
